Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at Pipefitters Local 537 in Dorchester, Massachusetts, expressing gratitude for the support of labor unions and highlighting the importance of investing in American workers. She emphasized the value of all labor and the need for workers to be acknowledged and compensated fairly. Harris praised the partnership between the government and labor unions, recognizing the role of unions in securing workers' rights and advocating for fair negotiations through collective bargaining. She also discussed the significance of apprenticeship programs in developing skilled workers and creating opportunities for individuals, especially those from marginalized communities. Harris encouraged the audience to continue fighting for workers' rights and to stand together in unity to build a better future.